{"word":"οὖς","slug":"οὖς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>οὖς, ὠτός, τό</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> auris ‘ear’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘organ of hearing’, <b>ear <a href='B:470 10:27'>Mt 10:27</a>; <a href='B:470 13:16'>13:16</a>; <a href='B:480 7:33'>Mk 7:33</a>; <a href='B:490 1:44'>Lk 1:44</a>; <a href='B:490 4:21'>4:21</a>; <a href='B:490 12:3'>12:3</a>; <a href='B:490 22:50'>22:50</a>; <a href='B:510 7:57'>Ac 7:57</a>; <a href='B:530 2:9'>1 Cor 2:9</a>; <a href='B:530 12:16'>12:16</a>; <a href='B:660 5:4'>Js 5:4</a>; <a href='B:670 3:12'>1 Pt 3:12</a>.</b> In <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ transf.\">transf.</a> sense<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘faculty of understanding or perception’, in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> relative to divine communication, <b>ear</b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘in one ear and out the other’) <b><a href='B:470 11:15'>Mt 11:15</a>; <a href='B:470 13:15'>13:15f</a>; <a href='B:480 7:16'>Mk 7:16</a>; <a href='B:490 9:44'>Lk 9:44</a>; <a href='B:490 14:35'>14:35</a>; <a href='B:510 7:51'>Ac 7:51</a>; <a href='B:510 28:27'>28:27</a>; <a href='B:520 11:8'>Ro 11:8</a>; <a href='B:730 2:7'>Rv 2:7</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Rv; prophetic diagnosis: <el>τοῖς ὠσὶν <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βαρέως\">βαρέως</a> ἀϰούειν</el> hear with unreceptive ears <b><a href='B:470 13:15'>Mt 13:15</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Οὐρίας\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:οὐσία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}